    "page": 7,
    "block_id": "page_007:block_051",
    "block_type": "text",
    "text": "post-fix version of files modified by the commit. 𝑀 𝑑𝑒𝑙 _ 𝑙𝑖𝑛𝑒𝑠 : The set of methods containing deleted lines of code from the fix commit (identified based on the pre-fix version). 𝑀 𝑎𝑑𝑑 _ 𝑙𝑖𝑛𝑒𝑠 : The set of methods containing added lines of code from the fix commit (identified based on the post-fix version). We classify method changes into five types based on these sets to reduce irrelevant information and enhance the LLM’s focus. ① Methods with only line deletions: 𝑚 ∈ ( 𝑀 𝑝𝑟𝑒 ∩ 𝑀 𝑝𝑜𝑠𝑡 ∩ 𝑀 𝑑𝑒𝑙 _ 𝑙𝑖𝑛𝑒𝑠 ) \\ 𝑀 𝑎𝑑𝑑 _ 𝑙𝑖𝑛𝑒𝑠 . ② Completely deleted methods: 𝑚 ∈ 𝑀 𝑝𝑟𝑒 \\ 𝑀 𝑝𝑜𝑠𝑡 . ③ Methods with only line additions: 𝑚 ∈( 𝑀 𝑝𝑟𝑒 ∩ 𝑀 𝑝𝑜𝑠𝑡 ∩ 𝑀 𝑎𝑑𝑑 _ 𝑙𝑖𝑛𝑒𝑠 ) \\ 𝑀 𝑑𝑒𝑙 _ 𝑙𝑖𝑛𝑒𝑠 . ④ Methods with both line additions and deletions: 𝑚 ∈ 𝑀 𝑝𝑟𝑒 ∩ 𝑀 𝑝𝑜𝑠𝑡 ∩ 𝑀 𝑑𝑒𝑙 _ 𝑙𝑖𝑛𝑒𝑠 ∩ 𝑀 𝑎𝑑𝑑 _ 𝑙𝑖𝑛𝑒𝑠 . ⑤ Newly added methods: 𝑚 ∈ 𝑀 𝑝𝑜𝑠𝑡 \\ 𝑀 𝑝𝑟𝑒 .",
