    "text": "• CWE (Common Weakness Enumeration). CWE is a community-maintained classification standard for software and hardware security weaknesses, aimed at systematically describing common weaknesses in code, design, or logic (e.g., root causes of vulnerabilities). It reveals the mechanism behind the vulnerability.",
